    • Method Detail

      • handleResponse

        public void handleResponse​(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response,
                           java.lang.String location,
                           java.util.Date fromDate,
                           java.util.Date toDate)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        Uses an ItemListFinder to obtain a list of items based on query parameters and writes the list to the HTTP servlet response object in a CSV format.
        Parameters:
        location - The location of interest.
        fromDate - The start date for the data (inclusive).
        toDate - The end date for the data (inclusive).
        response - Data is written to the writer of the response object and the content type is set to text/csv.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown if there is a problem obtaining the writer of the response object.
